WEBVTT

00:15.460 --> 00:16.700
CHAPTER VII

00:17.190 --> 00:20.140
Then said the High Priest, Are these things so?

00:20.420 --> 00:23.920
And he said, Men, brethren, and fathers, hearken!

00:24.240 --> 00:29.540
The God of glory appeared unto our father Abraham when he was in Mesopotamia, before

00:29.540 --> 00:35.660
he dwelt in Charon, and said unto him, Get thee out of thy country and from thy kindred,

00:35.960 --> 00:38.380
and come into the land which I shall show thee.

00:38.800 --> 00:44.700
Then came he out of the land of the Chaldeans, and dwelt in Charon, and from thence, when

00:44.700 --> 00:49.980
his father was dead, he removed him into this land wherein ye now dwell.

00:50.400 --> 00:56.640
And he gave him none inheritance in it, no, not so much as to set his foot on, yet he

00:57.060 --> 01:02.760
would give it to him for a possession, and to his seed after him, when as yet he had

01:02.760 --> 01:03.660
no child.

01:04.060 --> 01:09.920
And God spake on this wise, that his seed should sojourn in a strange land, and that

01:09.920 --> 01:14.600
they should bring them into bondage and entreat them evil four hundred years.

01:15.020 --> 01:21.220
And the nation to whom they shall be in bondage will I judge, said God, and after that shall

01:21.220 --> 01:23.940
they come forth and serve me in this place.

01:24.620 --> 01:30.340
And he gave him the covenant of circumcision, and so Abraham begat Isaac and circumcised

01:30.340 --> 01:36.460
him the eighth day, and Isaac begat Jacob, and Jacob begat the twelve patriarchs.

01:36.640 --> 01:42.700
And the patriarchs, moved with envy, sold Joseph into Egypt, but God was with him and

01:42.700 --> 01:47.620
delivered him out of all his afflictions, and gave him favor and wisdom in the sight

01:47.620 --> 01:53.120
of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, and he made him governor over Egypt and all his house.

01:53.660 --> 01:58.880
Now there came a dearth over all the land of Egypt and Chanan, and great affliction,

01:59.200 --> 02:01.620
and our fathers found no sustenance.

02:01.900 --> 02:07.060
But when Jacob heard that there was corn in Egypt, he sent out our fathers first, and

02:07.060 --> 02:12.340
at the second time Joseph was made known to his brethren, and Joseph's kindred was made

02:12.340 --> 02:13.560
known unto Pharaoh.

02:14.260 --> 02:20.340
Then sent Joseph, and called his father Jacob to him, and all his kindred, three score and

02:20.340 --> 02:21.500
fifteen souls.

02:22.180 --> 02:28.060
So Jacob went down into Egypt, and died, he and our fathers, and were carried over to

02:28.060 --> 02:33.300
Secum, and laid in the sepulcher that Abraham bought for a sum of money of the sons of Amor,

02:33.400 --> 02:34.640
the father of Secum.

02:35.280 --> 02:40.360
But when the time of the promise drew nigh, which God had sworn to Abraham, the people

02:40.360 --> 02:45.360
grew and multiplied in Egypt, till another king arose which knew not Joseph.

02:45.920 --> 02:51.680
The same dealt subtly with our kindred, and evil entreated our fathers, so that they cast

02:51.680 --> 02:55.160
out their young children, to the end they might not live.

02:55.660 --> 03:01.880
In which time Moses was born, and was exceeding fair, and nourished up in his father's house

03:01.880 --> 03:02.840
three months.

03:03.260 --> 03:08.420
And when he was cast out, Pharaoh's daughter took him up, and nourished him for her own

03:08.420 --> 03:08.860
son.

03:08.860 --> 03:14.560
And Moses was learned in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was mighty in words and

03:14.560 --> 03:15.260
in deeds.

03:15.720 --> 03:21.140
And when he was full forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brethren the children

03:21.140 --> 03:21.900
of Israel.

03:22.360 --> 03:28.500
And seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him that was oppressed and

03:28.500 --> 03:33.760
smote the Egyptian, for he supposed his brethren would have understood how that God by his

03:33.760 --> 03:37.180
hand would deliver them, but they understood not.

03:37.680 --> 03:42.960
And the next day he showed himself unto them as they strove, and would have set them at

03:42.960 --> 03:44.200
one again, saying,

03:44.820 --> 03:49.100
"'Sirs ye our brethren, why do ye wrong one to another?'

03:49.100 --> 03:52.960
But he that did his neighbor wrong thrust him away, saying,

03:53.000 --> 03:56.060
"'Who made thee a ruler and a judge over us?

03:56.420 --> 04:00.420
Wilt thou kill me as thou didst the Egyptian yesterday?'

04:00.420 --> 04:06.140
Then fled Moses at this saying, and was a stranger in the land of Median, where he beget

04:06.140 --> 04:07.040
two sons.

04:07.540 --> 04:12.980
And when forty years were expired, there appeared to him in the wilderness of Mount Sinai an

04:12.980 --> 04:15.800
angel of the Lord in a flame of fire in a bush.

04:16.320 --> 04:21.820
When Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight, and as he drew near to behold it, the voice

04:21.820 --> 04:23.980
of the Lord came unto him, saying,

04:24.000 --> 04:29.020
"'I am the God of thy fathers, the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God

04:29.020 --> 04:30.220
of Jacob.'

04:30.220 --> 04:33.260
Then Moses trembled, and durst not behold.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.500
Then said the Lord to him,

04:35.860 --> 04:40.600
"'Put off thy shoes from thy feet, for the place where thou standest is holy ground.

04:41.080 --> 04:46.660
I have seen, I have seen the affliction of my people, which is in Egypt, and I have heard

04:46.660 --> 04:49.820
their groaning, and am come down to deliver them.

04:50.060 --> 04:53.620
And now come, I will send thee into Egypt.'

04:53.620 --> 04:56.300
This Moses whom they refused, saying,

04:56.460 --> 04:58.480
Who made thee a ruler and a judge?

04:58.840 --> 05:03.860
The same did God send to be a ruler and a deliverer by the hand of the angel which appeared

05:03.860 --> 05:05.000
to him in the bush.

05:05.680 --> 05:10.860
He brought them out, after that he had showed wonders and signs in the land of Egypt, and

05:10.860 --> 05:14.080
in the Red Sea, and in the wilderness forty years.

05:14.700 --> 05:18.100
This is that Moses which said unto the children of Israel,

05:18.400 --> 05:23.920
"'A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you, of your brethren, like unto me,

05:24.240 --> 05:26.260
him shall ye hear.'

05:26.260 --> 05:31.640
This is he that was in the church in the wilderness with the angel which spake to him in the

05:31.640 --> 05:38.860
Mount Sinai, and with our fathers, who received the lively oracles to give unto us, to whom

05:38.860 --> 05:44.060
our fathers would not obey but thrust him from them, and in their hearts turned back

05:44.060 --> 05:51.000
again into Egypt, saying unto Aaron, Make us gods to go before us, for as for this Moses

05:51.000 --> 05:56.360
which brought us out of the land of Egypt, we want not what has become of him.'

05:56.360 --> 06:02.060
And they made a calf in those days, and offered sacrifice unto the idol, and rejoiced in the

06:02.060 --> 06:03.440
works of their own hands.

06:03.980 --> 06:09.060
Then God turned and gave them up to worship the host of heaven, as it is written in the

06:09.060 --> 06:15.300
Book of the Prophets, O ye house of Israel, have ye offered to me slain beasts and sacrifices

06:15.300 --> 06:17.880
by the space of forty years in the wilderness?

06:17.880 --> 06:23.880
Yea, ye took up the tabernacle of Moloch, and the star of your God Remphan, figures

06:23.880 --> 06:25.800
which ye made to worship them.

06:26.080 --> 06:28.960
And I will carry you away beyond Babylon.

06:29.560 --> 06:35.260
Our fathers had the tabernacle of witness in the wilderness, as he had appointed, speaking

06:35.260 --> 06:40.960
unto Moses, that he should make it according to the fashion that he had seen, which also

06:40.960 --> 06:46.440
our fathers, that came after, brought in with Jesus into the possession of the Gentiles,

06:46.440 --> 06:52.040
whom God drove out before the face of our fathers, unto the days of David, who found

06:52.040 --> 06:56.460
favor before God, and desired to find a tabernacle for the God of Jacob.

06:57.080 --> 06:59.380
But Solomon built him in house.

06:59.920 --> 07:05.760
Howbeit the Most High dwelleth not in temples made with hands, as saith the prophet, Heaven

07:05.760 --> 07:08.160
is my throne, and earth is my footstool.

07:08.540 --> 07:13.220
What house will ye build me, saith the Lord, or what is the place of my rest?

07:13.220 --> 07:16.220
Hath not my hand made all these things?

07:17.060 --> 07:23.020
Ye stiff-necked and uncircumcised in heart and ears, ye do always resist the Holy Ghost,

07:23.240 --> 07:25.840
as your fathers did, so do ye.

07:26.280 --> 07:31.260
Which of the prophets have not your fathers persecuted, and they have slain them which

07:31.260 --> 07:36.660
showed before of the coming of the Just One, of whom ye have been now the betrayers and

07:36.660 --> 07:43.340
murderers, who have received the law by the disposition of angels, and have not kept it?

07:43.880 --> 07:48.420
When they heard these things, they were cut to the heart, and they gnashed on him with

07:48.420 --> 07:49.260
their teeth.

07:49.780 --> 07:55.700
But he, being full of the Holy Ghost, looked up steadfastly into heaven, and saw the glory

07:55.700 --> 08:01.960
of God, and Jesus standing on the right hand of God, and said, Behold, I see the heavens

08:01.960 --> 08:05.400
opened, and the Son of Man standing on the right hand of God.

08:06.060 --> 08:11.100
Then they cried out with a loud voice, and stopped their ears, and ran upon him with

08:11.100 --> 08:17.260
one accord, and cast him out of the city, and stoned him, and the witnesses laid down

08:17.260 --> 08:20.740
their clothes at a young man's feet, whose name was Saul.

08:21.260 --> 08:27.260
And they stoned Stephen, calling upon God, and saying, Lord Jesus, receive my spirit.

08:27.800 --> 08:33.540
And he kneeled down, and cried with a loud voice, Lord, lay not this sin to their charge.

08:33.900 --> 08:36.780
And when he had said this, he fell asleep.

08:37.940 --> 08:39.080
CHAPTER VIII.

08:39.440 --> 08:44.660
And Saul was consenting unto his death, and at that time there was a great persecution

08:44.660 --> 08:49.740
against the church which was at Jerusalem, and they were all scattered abroad throughout

08:49.740 --> 08:53.740
the regions of Judea and Samaria, except the apostles.

08:54.260 --> 08:59.600
And devout men carried Stephen to his burial, and made great lamentation over him.

08:59.600 --> 09:05.880
As for Saul, he made havoc of the church, entering into every house, and howling men

09:05.880 --> 09:07.920
and women committed them to prison.

09:08.600 --> 09:12.660
Therefore, they that were scattered abroad went everywhere preaching the word.

09:13.240 --> 09:18.000
Then Philip went down to the city of Samaria, and preached Christ unto them.

09:18.340 --> 09:23.600
And the people, with one accord, gave heed unto those things which Philip spake, hearing

09:23.600 --> 09:25.820
and seeing the miracles which he did.

09:26.220 --> 09:31.420
For unclean spirits, crying with loud voice, came out of many that were possessed with

09:31.420 --> 09:36.060
them, and many taken with palsies, and that were lame, were healed.

09:36.580 --> 09:38.840
And there was great joy in that city.

09:39.460 --> 09:45.120
But there was a certain man, called Simon, which before time in the same city used sorcery,

09:45.380 --> 09:50.940
and bewitched the people of Samaria, giving out that himself was some great one, to whom

09:50.940 --> 09:56.180
they all gave heed, from the least to the greatest, saying, This man is the great power

09:56.180 --> 09:56.920
of God.

09:57.200 --> 10:02.880
And to him they had regard, because that of long time he had bewitched them with sorceries.

10:03.400 --> 10:07.880
But when they believed Philip, preaching the things concerning the kingdom of God, and

10:07.880 --> 10:11.900
the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized both men and women.

10:12.400 --> 10:14.880
Then Simon himself believed also.

10:15.120 --> 10:20.260
And when he was baptized, he continued with Philip, and wondered, beholding the miracles

10:20.260 --> 10:21.840
and signs which were done.

10:22.480 --> 10:27.540
Now when the apostles which were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of

10:27.540 --> 10:33.840
God, they sent unto them Peter and John, who, when they were come down, prayed for them,

10:34.040 --> 10:39.760
that they might receive the Holy Ghost, for as yet he was fallen upon none of them, only

10:39.760 --> 10:42.360
they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.

10:42.940 --> 10:47.180
Then laid they their hands on them, and they received the Holy Ghost.

10:47.180 --> 10:52.780
And when Simon saw that through laying on of the apostles hands the Holy Ghost was given,

10:53.160 --> 10:59.360
he offered them money, saying, Give me also this power, that on whomsoever I lay hands,

10:59.680 --> 11:01.380
he may receive the Holy Ghost.

11:01.860 --> 11:07.500
But Peter said unto him, Thy money perish with thee, because thou hast thought that

11:07.500 --> 11:10.080
the gift of God may be purchased with money.

11:10.080 --> 11:16.080
Thou hast neither part nor lot in this matter, for thy heart is not right in the sight of

11:16.080 --> 11:16.500
God.

11:17.160 --> 11:22.480
Repent therefore of this thy wickedness, and pray God if perhaps the thought of thine heart

11:22.480 --> 11:27.880
may be forgiven thee, for I perceive that thou art in the gall of bitterness and in

11:27.880 --> 11:29.220
the bond of iniquity.

11:29.880 --> 11:35.220
Then answered Simon and said, Pray ye to the Lord for me, that none of these things which

11:35.220 --> 11:37.220
ye have spoken come upon me.

11:37.820 --> 11:42.960
And they, when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem

11:42.960 --> 11:46.780
and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.

11:47.860 --> 11:53.340
And the angel of the Lord spake unto Philip, saying, Arise and go toward the south unto

11:53.340 --> 11:57.660
the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is desert.

11:58.160 --> 11:59.780
And he arose and went.

12:00.080 --> 12:05.700
And behold, a man of Ethiopia, and eunuch of great authority under Candace, queen of

12:05.700 --> 12:11.060
the Ethiopians, who had the charge of all her treasure and had come to Jerusalem for

12:11.060 --> 12:16.840
to worship, was returning and sitting in his chariot read Isaias the prophet.

12:17.520 --> 12:22.580
Then the spirit said unto Philip, Go near and join thyself to this chariot.

12:23.140 --> 12:29.560
And Philip ran thither to him and heard him read the prophet Isaias, and said, Understandest

12:29.560 --> 12:31.040
thou what thou readest?

12:31.040 --> 12:35.580
And he said, How can I except some man should guide me?

12:35.820 --> 12:39.200
And he desired Philip that he would come up and sit with him.

12:39.920 --> 12:45.240
The place of the scripture which he read was this, He was led as a sheep to the slaughter,

12:45.640 --> 12:50.040
and like a lamb done before his shearer, so opened he not his mouth.

12:50.420 --> 12:56.080
In his humiliation his judgment was taken away, and who shall declare his generation,

12:56.520 --> 12:58.760
for his life is taken from the earth.

12:59.400 --> 13:04.980
And the eunuch answered Philip, and said, I pray thee, of whom speaketh the prophet this,

13:05.180 --> 13:07.500
of himself or of some other man?

13:07.900 --> 13:13.740
Then Philip opened his mouth, and began at the same scripture, and preached unto him Jesus.

13:14.420 --> 13:18.080
And as they went on their way, they came unto a certain water.

13:18.380 --> 13:23.780
And the eunuch said, See, here is water, what doth hinder me to be baptized?

13:23.780 --> 13:29.040
And Philip said, If thou believest with all thine heart, thou mayest.

13:29.240 --> 13:33.820
And he answered and said, I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God.

13:34.280 --> 13:39.180
And he commanded the chariot to stand still, and they went down both into the water,

13:39.440 --> 13:42.680
both Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him.

13:43.100 --> 13:47.760
And when they were come up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught away Philip,

13:48.200 --> 13:52.720
that the eunuch saw him no more, and he went on his way rejoicing.

13:53.280 --> 13:57.100
But Philip was found at Azotes, and passing through,

13:57.400 --> 14:00.720
he preached in all the cities, till he came to Caesarea.

